<dl id="n05015a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05015a">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05015a"> 15(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Abel (pastoral heb. herder)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the language of Scripture, &ldquo;Cain brought of the fruit of the ground an offering unto the Lord. And <mark>Abel</mark>, he also brought of the firstlings of <mark>his flock</mark> and of the fat thereof. And the Lord had respect unto Abel and to his offering: But unto Cain and to his offering he had no respect.&rdquo; <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Cain and Abel] 42</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c02017j" href="c02all.htm#c02017j">VI.C.02:017(j)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
